"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":null,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"na","read":null,"meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":null,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"na","read":null,"meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":null,"unit":"% YoY","status":"na","read":null,"meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":null,"pe_percentile":null,"median_pe":null,"earnings_yield_pct":null,"pb":null,"ev_ebitda":null,"quality_score":null,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"na","read":null},"expectations":null,"cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[69.28,69.16,69.06,69.02,68.94,68.93,68.92,68.92,68.92,42.67,42.67],"latest_pct":42.67,"chg_1y_pp":-26.25},"FII":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[2.07,0.74,0.87,0.94,0.99,1.33,1.0,1.85,1.68,11.8,11.49],"latest_pct":11.49,"chg_1y_pp":10.49},"DII":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[12.99,11.3,9.82,10.6,10.01,8.23,7.04,2.78,2.39,9.74,9.56],"latest_pct":9.56,"chg_1y_pp":2.52},"Government":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[0.0,0.0,0.0,0.01,0.01,0.01,0.01,0.01,0.01,0.03,0.02],"latest_pct":0.02,"chg_1y_pp":0.01},"Public":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[15.67,18.8,20.25,19.43,20.04,21.5,23.04,26.43,27.0,35.76,36.27],"latest_pct":36.27,"chg_1y_pp":13.23}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"12-Jul-2024","subject":"Dividend - Re 0.50 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"14-Oct-2025","subject":"Rights 8:13 @ Premium Rs 4/-","materiality":"High"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchabl